(191, 2, '2013-02-01 18:14:10', '2013-02-01 18:14:10', '<p>Charter schools aren\'t just passing kids along says Queeney Fortson, who said she saw too much of that when she worked for Los Angeles Unified School District (LAUSD). That\'s why she <a href="/2012/11/parents-win---lausd-board-votes-down-zimmer-resolution.html">joined hundreds of other parents in front of the school district to represent her child\'s school - Aspire - and speak out in favor of charter schools</a>.</p>\n\n<div class="video-container"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/4Xb6VPKsUNI" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n', 'VIDEO: Aspire is inspiring and motivating our kids', 'Charter schools aren\'t just passing kids along says Queeney Fortson, who said she saw too much of that when she worked for Los Angeles Unified School District (LAUSD). Now her daughter is attending an Aspire charter school.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'video_aspire_is_inspiring_and_motivating_our_kids', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:20', '2016-01-13 04:22:20', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/video_aspire_is_inspiring_and_motivating_our_kids/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(192, 2, '2013-02-04 11:36:22', '2013-02-04 11:36:22', '<p>Our democracy is only as strong as the citizens that participate in it. Every day, elected officials make decisions that affect our schools and our children. Parents are their children\'s best advocates and when parents are involved, elected officials listen. Your vote is your voice! That\'s why it is so important to participate in elections.\nWhen you vote, you set a great example for your kids and show them citizenship in action! There are lots of ways to engage other parents at your school and help educate and involve them in upcoming elections.</p>\n\n<table border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">\n<tr>\n<th width="50%" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"><span style="font-size:16px; text-align:center; font-weight:bold;"> DO </span>\n</th>\n<th width="50%" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"><span style="font-size:16px; text-align:center; font-weight:bold;">DON\'T\n</span></th>\n<tr>\n<td width="391" valign="top"><p><strong>Educate</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Sign up parents to    Families That Can</li>\n<li>Distribute    non-partisan materials about upcoming elections, including candidates and/or    ballot measures, as long as the materials provide <em>neutral</em>&nbsp;information    and do not advocate a position or endorsement</li>\n<li>Include information    about the upcoming election and how to vote in your school newsletter</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Empower</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Sponsor non-partisan    candidate forums or debates, inviting all the candidates</li>\n<li>Help people register    to vote and understand the elections and voting process</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Mobilize</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Remind parents of key    deadlines</li>\n<li>Encourage and help    people to get to the polls on election day, regardless of how they intend to    vote</li>\n</ul></td>\n<td width="341" valign="top"><p><strong>Use school resources to support a specific candidate or ballot    measure</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Use school funds or    equipment to support or oppose candidates or ballot measures like copying    flyers in favor of a candidate on the school copy machine or using the    school\'s robo-call system</li>\n<li>Endorse candidates for    office or tell parents who to vote for</li>\n<li>Use school funds to    make contributions to candidates or ballot measure campaigns</li>\n<li>Let candidates use your    school\'s office space, equipment, or other resources</li>\n<li>Rate candidates</li>\n</ul></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<h3>What Does Partisan vs. Non-partisan Mean?</h3>\n\n<p>Partisan means being clearly in favor of one candidate or ballot measure over another. A handout saying "Vote for Jose Ramirez for School Board!" is partisan. A flyer with unbiased information about all the candidates in the race or their answers to a survey is non-partisan.\n- If you have a handout with candidate information, include the same information for ALL candidates.\n- If you invite candidates to your school event, invite ALL candidates.</p>\n\n<h3>Does this mean I can\'t speak in support of the candidate I like?</h3>\n\n<p>As a citizen, it is your right to speak your opinion and support the candidates and ballot measures you believe in. The Do\'s and Don\'ts above refer to the activities you can do to engage fellow parents on your school campus and using school resources.\nThere are tons of other ways to participate in local campaigns on your own time like:\n- Endorsing a candidate and having your name included on their campaign literature\n- Being in photos with the candidate you support for their mailer\n- Speaking in favor of the candidate on your Facebook and Twitter or other social media networks\n- Wearing your t-shirt or button in favor of the candidate\n- Volunteering for the candidate\'s campaign\n- Holding an event at your house for people to meet the candidate\n- Organizing a fundraiser for the candidate or donating money to the campaign\n- Passing out campaign flyers or holding up posters - DON\'T pass out campaign flyers on the school campus, but you can stand on the sidewalk, which is public land</p>\n\n<h3>What if I also am an employee of the school?</h3>\n\n<p>You can still do anything you want on your own time - just don\'t do partisan activities during your work hours, on the school campus or using school resources like your work computer or the school copy machine.</p>\n\n<h3>More Resources</h3>\n\n<p><a href="http://www.ccsa.org/civics">Learn more about ways schools can promote civic engagement</a>, including our "FAQ on Candidates and Ballot Measures" especially for school leaders. *These resources are for CCSA members only. If your school is a member of the California Charter Schools Association, ask your school leader for access.</p>\n', 'A Parent\'s Guide to Elections Outreach at Your School', 'Our democracy is only as strong as the citizens that participate in it. Learn how you can get parents involved and informed about important upcoming elections!\n', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'a_parents_guide_to_elections_outreach_at_your_school', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:20', '2016-01-13 04:22:20', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/a_parents_guide_to_elections_outreach_at_your_school/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(193, 2, '2013-02-04 12:46:01', '2013-02-04 12:46:01', '<p>Nuestra democracia es tan fuerte como los ciudadanos que participan en ella.  Todos los días, los funcionarios electos toman decisiones que afectan a nuestras escuelas y a nuestros hijos.  Los padres son los mejores defensores de sus hijos y, cuando ellos participan, los funcionarios electos los escuchan. ¡Su voto es su voz! Por eso es que es tan importante participar en las elecciones.\nCuando usted vota, ¡les da un gran ejemplo a sus hijos y les muestra lo que es actuar como un ciudadano! Hay muchas formas en las que se puede involucrar a otros padres en su escuela y ayudarlos a que se informen y participen en las próximas elecciones.</p>\n\n<table border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">\n<tr>\n<th width="50%" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"><span style="font-size:16px; text-align:center; font-weight:bold;"> QUÉ HACER</span>\n</th>\n<th width="50%" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"><span style="font-size:16px; text-align:center; font-weight:bold;">QUÉ NO HACER\n</span></th>\n<tr>\n<td width="391" valign="top"><p><strong>Educarse</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Regístrense como padres  en Families That Can</li>\n<li>Distribuyan materiales  apartidistas sobre las próximas elecciones, incluyendo a los candidatos y/o las  medidas que estarán en la boleta, así como materiales que ofrezcan información  neutral y no apoyen o defiendan una determinada posición. </li>\n<li>Incluyan información  sobre las próximas elecciones y sobre cómo votar en el siguiente boletín de su  escuela.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Empoderar</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Patrocinen foros o  debates apartidistas entre candidatos, inviten a todos ellos.</li>\n<li>Ayuden a la gente a  registrarse para votar y a entender las elecciones y el proceso de votación.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Movilizarse</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Recuerden  a los padres las fechas claves.</li>\n<li>Animen  y ayuden a las personas a ir a votar el día de la elección, al margen de cómo  piensen votar.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td width="341" valign="top"><p><strong>Usar  los recursos de la escuela para apoyar a un candidato o medida específica</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Usar los fondos  escolares o el equipo de la escuela para apoyar u oponerse a candidatos o  medidas en la boleta electoral como hacer copias de volantes a favor de un  candidato con una copiadora de la escuela o usar el sistema de llamadas de la escuela. </li>\n<li>Apoyar a candidatos para  un puesto o decirle a otros padres por quién votar. </li>\n<li>Usar los fondos de la  escuela para hacer contribuciones para campañas de candidatos o  medidas en la boleta electoral.</li>\n<li>Permitir que los  candidatos usen el espacio de oficina de la escuela, el equipo u otros  recursos.</li>\n<li>Calificar a los candidatos.</li></ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<h3>¿Qué significa partidista y no partidista?</h3>\n\n<p>Partidista significa estar claramente a favor de un candidato o medida  por encima de otra. Un volante que diga "¡Vote por José Ramírez para la Junta Escolar"! es partidista. Un volante con información neutral acerca de todos los candidatos en la competencia o sus respuestas en una encuesta es  no partidista.\n- Si tiene un volante con información de un candidato, incluya la misma información de TODOS los candidatos.\n- Si invita a los candidatos a un evento de su escuela, invite a TODOS los candidatos.</p>\n\n<h3>¿Esto significa que no puedo hablar a favor del candidato que yo prefiero?</h3>\n\n<p>Como ciudadano, es su derecho de expresar su opinión y apoyar a los candidatos y medidas en la boleta electoral en los que usted crea. Los puntos de arriba sobre lo que se debe hacer y lo que no se debe hacer se refieren a las actividades que usted puede realizar para invitar a participar a otros padres en el campus de su escuela y usando los recursos escolares. Hay muchas otras formas de participar en su propio tiempo como:\n- Apoyar a un candidato y tener su nombre incluido en la literatura de su campaña.\n- Estar en fotos con el candidato que usted apoya para los correos que él o ella manda.\n- Hablar a favor del candidato en su página de  Facebook, en Twitter y otras redes sociales.\n- Llevar en su ropa un botón a favor del candidato.\n- Ser voluntario en la campaña del candidato.\n- Hacer un evento en su casa para que la gente se reúna con el candidato.\n- Organizar un evento de recaudación de fondos para el candidato o donar dinero a su campaña.\nDistribuir volantes de la campaña o colocar carteles de los candidatos o medidas en la boleta.   NO puede hacer esto en el campus de la escuela, pero sí en la acera, que es terreno público.</p>\n\n<h3>¿Qué pasa si soy también un empleado de la escuela?</h3>\n\n<p>Usted puede hacer lo que desee en su tiempo libre, solamente tenga cuidado de no hacer actividades partidistas durante sus horas de trabajo, en el campus de la escuela y tampoco use recursos de la escuela, como la computadora o la copiadora.</p>\n\n<h3>Más Recursos</h3>\n\n<p>Aprenda más sobre la forma en que las escuelas pueden promover la participación cívica en  <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/civics">www.ccsa.org/civics</a>.</p>\n', 'Una Guía Para Los Padres Sobre Elecciones', 'Nuestra democracia es tan fuerte como los ciudadanos que participan en ella. ¡Aprenda como correr la voz sobre las elecciones en su escuela!\n', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'una_guia_para_los_padres_sobre_elecciones', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:20', '2016-01-13 04:22:20', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/una_guia_para_los_padres_sobre_elecciones/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(194, 2, '2013-02-04 13:33:24', '2013-02-04 13:33:24', '<p>As a parent, how can you bring a new high-quality charter school to your community?What is the process for starting a charter school?\nFind out answers to these questions and more on February 20th at the second Sacramento Start-Up Circle, presented by the California Charter Schools Association (CCSA)!\nYou\'ll discuss and share strategies to engage the community in launching a new school with Erin Marston, Founding Principal, <a href="http://www.williamleecollegeprep.org/">William Lee College Prep.</a>\nEvery event of the Start-Up Circle is an opportunity to learn more about the process of starting a charter school, find out about supports are available to teams interested in starting a charter school, and connect with others who want more high-quality public schools in California.\nThis event will be held on Wednesday, February 20th at 5:30 pm at William Lee College Prep, 3300 Stockton Blvd., Sacramento, CA. <a href="http://www.meetup.com/startupcircle/">Please RSVP here.</a>\nCan\'t make it? <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/starting/">Learn more about how to start a charter school!</a></p>\n', 'Feb. 20: Start-up Circle in Sacramento', 'As a parent, how can you bring a new high-quality charter school to your community? Learn more at this free event!\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'feb_20_start-up_circle_in_sacramento', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:19', '2016-01-13 04:22:19', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/feb_20_start-up_circle_in_sacramento/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(195, 2, '2013-02-04 13:41:56', '2013-02-04 13:41:56', '<p>As a parent, how can you bring a new high-quality charter school to your community? What is the process for starting a charter school?\nFind out answers to these questions and more on February 20th at the second Sacramento Start-Up Circle, presented by the California Charter Schools Association (CCSA)!\nYou\'ll have the opportunity to hear from <a href="http://www.pactsj.org/">PACT parent leaders</a> about demand for new schools in San José and discover how a group of committed parents and educators worked together to launch <a href="http://www.alphapublicschools.org/our-schools/alpha-middle-school/">Alpha: Blanca Alvarado Middle School.</a>\nEvery event of the Start-Up Circle is an opportunity to learn more about the process of starting a charter school, find out about supports are available to teams interested in starting a charter school, and connect with others who want more high-quality public schools in California.\nThis event will be held on Wednesday, February 13th at 5:30pm at Alpha: Blanca Alvarado Middle School, 1610 Cunningham Ave., San José, CA, February 20th at 5:30 pm at William Lee College Prep, 3300 Stockton Blvd., Sacramento, CA. <a href="http://www.meetup.com/startupcircle/">Please RSVP here.</a>\nCan\'t make it? <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/starting/">Learn more about how to start a charter school!</a></p>\n', 'Feb. 13: Start-up Circle in San Jose', 'As a parent, how can you bring a new high-quality charter school to your community? Learn more at this free event!\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'feb_13_start-up_circle_in_san_jose', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:19', '2016-01-13 04:22:19', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/feb_13_start-up_circle_in_san_jose/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(196, 2, '2013-02-04 13:58:26', '2013-02-04 13:58:26', '"Shelby is 13 and she\'s in 6th grade, and up until last year, she was never in any grade," says her mom. Thanks to Aspire Alexander Twilight College Preparatory Academy in Sacramento, that\'s no longer the case. Learn how one California charter school is using an innovative approach to special education to benefit all students.\n<div class="video-container"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/y8Wnq_ouyWs?list=PL5E21E12E78B555CB" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n###Learn more.\nCharter Schools and Special Education: FAQs for Families\nhttp://www.ccsa.org/2010/11/charter-schools-and-special-education-frequently-asked-questions-and-answers-for-families.html\n', 'VIDEO: Shelby\'s Story: "Paving the Way for Other Kids"', 'Learn how one California charter school is using an innovative approach to special education to benefit all students.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'video_shelbys_story_paving_the_way_for_other_kids', '', '', '2013-02-04 13:58:26', '2013-02-04 13:58:26', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/?p=196', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(197, 2, '2013-02-04 14:34:58', '2013-02-04 14:34:58', '<p>The United Way is hosting a community candidate forum:</p>\n\n<h3>LAUSD School Board Candidate Forum</h3>\n\n<p>Eastside\'s District 2\nWednesday, February 13, 2013\nRFK Community Schools\n701 S. Catalina St. LA, CA 90010\n6:00 pm - 7:30 pm\nInvited: Alberdo Diaz, Board President Mónica García, AnneMarie Montanez, Robert Skeels, Isabel Vazquez\nModerated discussion open to parents, students and community members\nFood, Childcare and Translation Provided</p>\n', 'Feb. 13: LAUSD Candidate Forum (Downtown and Eastside)', 'Charter school families are invited to meet the candidates for LAUSD board district 2!\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'feb_13_lausd_candidate_forum_downtown_and_eastside', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:19', '2016-01-13 04:22:19', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/feb_13_lausd_candidate_forum_downtown_and_eastside/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(198, 2, '2013-02-11 14:00:55', '2013-02-11 14:00:55', '<p>On March 5, families in the East San Fernando Valley will have the opportunity to vote for the board member who will represent our community on the Los Angeles Unified School District (LAUSD) board.\nThe seven LAUSD board members make major decisions that affect our children and our schools. <a href="/la2013">Learn more about the election on March 5!</a>\n<em>You\'re invited</em></p>\n\n<h3>LAUSD Candidate Forum for Charter School Families</h3>\n\n<p>Wednesday, February 27\n6:00 P.M.\nVaughn Charter/VISA Campus\n11505 Herrick St.\nPacoima, CA 91331\nMeet the Candidates for the East San Fernando Valley\n- Antonio Sanchez (Confirmed)\n- Maria Cano (Confirmed)\n- Monica Ratliff (Confirmed)\n<a href="/FTC_BD6_candidate_forum_flyer_BILINGUAL.pdf">Download the flyer to share.</a></p>\n', 'Feb. 27: LAUSD Candidate Forum for the East San Fernando Valley', 'Meet the candidates who want to represent you on the LAUSD board!\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'feb_27_lausd_candidate_forum_for_the_east_san_fernando_valley', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:19', '2016-01-13 04:22:19', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/feb_27_lausd_candidate_forum_for_the_east_san_fernando_valley/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(199, 2, '2013-02-11 14:03:28', '2013-02-11 14:03:28', '<p>En el 5 de marzo, las familias del Valle de San Fernando van a tener la oportunidad de votar quien va a representarles en la Junta Directiva del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Los Ángeles (LAUSD).\nLos siete miembros de la Junta Directiva del  LAUSD toman decisiones que afectan a nuestros niños y nuestras escuelas.\n<em>Está Invitado:</em></p>\n\n<h3>Foro de Candidatos para Las Familias de las Escuelas Chárter</h3>\n\n<p>Miércoles, 27 de febrero\n6:00 P.M.\nVaughn Charters/VISA Campus\n11505 Herrick St.\nPacoima, CA 91331\nConozca a los candidatos del este del Valle de San Fernando\n- Antonio Sanchez (Confirmado)\n- Maria Cano (Confirmada)\n- Monica Ratliff (Confirmada)\n<a href="/FTC_BD6_candidate_forum_flyer_BILINGUAL.pdf">Baje un folleto para compartir.</a></p>\n', '27 de febrero: Foro de Candidatos para el Este del Valle de San Fernando', 'Conozca a los candidatos que quieren representar a usted en la Junta Directiva del LAUSD.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '27_de_febrero_foro_de_candidatos_para_el_este_del_valle_de_san_fernando', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:19', '2016-01-13 04:22:19', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/27_de_febrero_foro_de_candidatos_para_el_este_del_valle_de_san_fernando/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(200, 2, '2013-02-21 11:05:50', '2013-02-21 11:05:50', '<p>The United Way hosted a forum with the candidates to represent Board District 2 for the Los Angeles Unified School District (LAUSD) board. They were asked to share their perspective on charter public schools - here\'s what they had to say!</p>\n\n<object width="400" height="224" >\n<param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" />\n<param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" />\n<param name="movie" value="http://www.facebook.com/v/10151440531454787" />\n<embed src="http://www.facebook.com/v/10151440531454787" type="application/x-shockwave-flash"\nallowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="400" height="224">\n</embed>\n</object>\n\n<object width="400" height="224" >\n<param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" />\n<param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" />\n<param name="movie" value="http://www.facebook.com/v/10151440758669787" />\n<embed src="http://www.facebook.com/v/10151440758669787" type="application/x-shockwave-flash"\nallowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="400" height="224">\n</embed>\n</object>\n\n<object width="400" height="224" >\n<param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" />\n<param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" />\n<param name="movie" value="http://www.facebook.com/v/10151440608639787" />\n<embed src="http://www.facebook.com/v/10151440608639787" type="application/x-shockwave-flash"\nallowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="400" height="224">\n</embed>\n</object>\n\n<object width="400" height="224" >\n<param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" />\n<param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" />\n<param name="movie" value="http://www.facebook.com/v/10151440738604787" />\n<embed src="http://www.facebook.com/v/10151440738604787" type="application/x-shockwave-flash"\nallowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="400" height="224">\n</embed>\n</object>\n', 'What the LAUSD Candidates Say About Charter Schools', 'There are dozens of charter public schools in the neighborhoods around downtown and East Los Angeles - What do the candidates to represent that area on the school board think?\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'what_the_lausd_candidates_say_about_charter_schools', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:19', '2016-01-13 04:22:19', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/what_the_lausd_candidates_say_about_charter_schools/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(201, 3, '2013-02-22 12:50:25', '2013-02-22 12:50:25', '<h3>Important LA School Board Election on March 5</h3>\n\n<p>On March 5, Angelenos have the opportunity to vote for three of the seven board members for the Los Angeles Unified School District (LAUSD). This is a very important election, not only for our school but for the future of our public schools and parent choice in Los Angeles.\nThe board makes major decisions that affect our school and our kids. This includes whether our charter school will be renewed and whether new charter schools can open and they have oversight of how our charter school is run - special education, budget and more.\nWe encourage everyone to get informed about this important election and to vote on March 5!\nLearn more at <a href="/la2013">www.familiesthatcan.org/la2013</a>.</p>\n\n<h3>Elección Importante para la Junta Escolar en el 5 de Marzo</h3>\n\n<p>En el 5 de marzo, los votantes de Los Angeles tendrán la oportunidad de votar para tres de los siete miembros del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Los Ángeles (LAUSD). Esta es una elección muy importante no solo para nuestra escuela sino para el futuro de la educación pública en Los Angeles.\nLos miembros de la Junta Directiva toman decisiones que afectan a nuestros niños y nuestras escuelas. Incluyen si se renovará el permiso a nuestras escuelas o se cerrarán y si una nueva escuela chárter puede abrir. También vigilan cómo operan nuestras escuelas chárter, desde los programas de educación especial hasta el presupuesto.\nAlentamos a todos informarse sobre la elección y ¡Votemos el 5 de marzo!\nAprende más en <a href="/la2013">www.familiesthatcan.org/la2013</a>.</p>\n', 'For your Newsletter: LAUSD Elections on March 5', 'A great way to spread the word about the elections is to include information in your school\'s newsletter. Feel free to adjust this text to reflect your school!\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'for_your_newsletter_lausd_elections_on_march_5', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:19', '2016-01-13 04:22:19', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/for_your_newsletter_lausd_elections_on_march_5/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(202, 3, '2013-02-25 10:10:58', '2013-02-25 10:10:58', '<p>Families That Can has created an easy-to-read, nonpartisan voter guide to help you learn more about the candidates running for the LA school board. Find out where candidates stand on education so that you can make informed decisions when you cast your ballot on May 21. The candidates for Board District 6 are:\n- Monica Ratliff\n- Antonio Sanchez\n*Update: The primary was held on March 5, 2013, with the vote split between several candidates. Candidate Maria Cano didn\'t make it through the primary - Monica Ratliff and Antonio Sanchez will go to a run-off on May 21.</p>\n\n<h4>Candidate Guide for the Los Angeles Unified School District (LAUSD) - Board District 6 (East San Fernando Valley)</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/BD6_LAUSD_FTC_Candidate_Guide_ENGLISH.pdf">English</a></li>\n<li><a href="/BD6_LAUSD_FTC_Candidate_Guide_SPANISH.pdf">Spanish</a>\nLearn more about the LAUSD election! <a href="/la2013">www.ccsafamilies/la2013</a></li>\n</ul>\n', 'LAUSD Candidate Guide for East San Fernando Valley', 'Families That Can has created an easy-to-read, nonpartisan voter guide to help you learn more about the candidates running for the LA school board.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'lausd_candidate_guide_for_east_san_fernando_valley', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:18', '2016-01-13 04:22:18', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/lausd_candidate_guide_for_east_san_fernando_valley/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(203, 3, '2013-02-25 10:14:03', '2013-02-25 10:14:03', '<p>En el 5 de marzo, las familias del Valle de San Fernando van a tener la oportunidad de votar quien va a representarles en la Junta Directiva del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Los Ángeles (LAUSD). Para ayudarles conocer a los candidatos, Families That Can ha creado este guía no partidista para el votante. Los tres candidatos son:\n- Maria Cano\n- Monica Ratliff\n- Antonio Sanchez\n<a href="/BD6_LAUSD_FTC_Candidate_Guide_SPANISH.pdf">Guía para la Junta de Educación del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Los Ángeles (LAUSD) - Distrito 6 de la Junta (Este del Valle de San Fernando)</a>\n<a href="/2013/01/decision-2013-eleccion-para-la-junta-directiva-del-lausd.html">Aprenda más sobre las elecciones.</a></p>\n', 'Guía para la Junta de Educación de Los Angeles -  Valle de San Fernando', 'Para ayudarles conocer a los candidatos, Families That Can ha creado este guía no partidista para el votante.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'guia_para_la_junta_de_educacion_de_los_angeles_-_valle_de_san_fernando', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:18', '2016-01-13 04:22:18', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/guia_para_la_junta_de_educacion_de_los_angeles_-_valle_de_san_fernando/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(204, 2, '2013-02-28 12:44:43', '2013-02-28 12:44:43', '<p>Hear what the candidates for the East San Fernando Valley had to say at the forum we hosted for charter school families on Feb. 27 at Vaughn Next Century Learning Center in Pacoima.\n- Voters like you decide on March 5 - <a href="/la2013">learn more about the election.</a>\n- <a href="/2013/02/lausd-candidate-guide-for-east-san-fernando-valley.html">See our non-partisan Candidate Guide.</a></p>\n\n<div class="video-container"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/xm3jP-9lS8Y" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n\n<p>To jump directly to the candidates\' answers on specific questions, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xm3jP-9lS8Y">click through here</a> and expand the description below the video for direct links.\n- 0:00 Opening Statements\n- 9:55 First question - Support for Dr Deasy\'s work to improve teacher evaluations\n- 16:20 Second question - Would you have supported the charter school moratorium proposed by Steve Zimmer?\n- 24:12 Third question - How will you include parents when you are making decisions on the board?\n- 31:22 Fourth question - How do you turn around low-performing schools, and how are charters involved in this?\n- 39:50 Fifth question - How will you ensure all charter schools have access to equitable facilities under Proposition 39?\n- 46:39 Sixth question - How will you ensure students are safe?\n- 53:15 Closing Statements</p>\n', 'VIDEO: LA School Board Candidate Forum', 'Hear what the candidates for the East San Fernando Valley had to say at the forum we hosted for charter school families on Feb. 27 at Vaughn Next Century Learning Center in Pacoima.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'video_la_school_board_candidate_forum', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:18', '2016-01-13 04:22:18', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/video_la_school_board_candidate_forum/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(205, 2, '2013-03-18 13:03:50', '2013-03-18 13:03:50', '<p>California parents are invited to join national parent and community leaders will join education reform advocates for the "Our Children, Our Choice" national conference call to discuss the legal rights of parents to provide their children with the best education possible.\nDespite parents wanting the best for their children, many are unaware of the educational options available to them. The aim of this call is to inform parents of their legal rights of parental choice and mobilize activists to spread the message of choice to their communities.\nThe event is co-hosted by Connecticut Parents Union, State of Black Connecticut, Democrats for Education Reform California, Moms for School Choice, Texas Parents Union, and the New York City Parents Union.\n- What: National Parental Choice Conference Call &amp; Webinar\n- When: Thursday, March 21st, 2013, 7:00 PM - 8:30 PM (EST)\n- Where: Call-in number: (559) 546-1880 - Access Code: 904418\n- Who: Parents from across the country, including Hamlet Garcia, a Pennsylvania parent facing up to seven years imprisonment for education theft; Dr. Howard Fuller, Black Alliance for Educational Options; Dr. Steve Perry, Principal, Capital Preparatory Magnet School, Hartford, Connecticut and best selling author; Sen. Gloria Romero (Ret.), author of nation\'s first Parent Trigger law and California State Director of Democrats for Education Reform (DFER); Rep. Alisha Thomas Morgan, author of public school choice legislation in Georgia, sponsor of "Amendment One: The Charter School Amendment," and sponsor of the "Parent Teacher Empowerment Act."</p>\n', 'March 21: National Conference Call on Legal Right of Parental Choice', 'California parents are invited to join national parent and community leaders will join education reform advocates for the "Our Children, Our Choice" national conference call to discuss the legal rights of parents to provide their children with the best education possible.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'march_21_national_conference_call_on_legal_right_of_parental_choice', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:18', '2016-01-13 04:22:18', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/march_21_national_conference_call_on_legal_right_of_parental_choice/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(206, 2, '2013-03-18 13:46:39', '2013-03-18 13:46:39', '<h3>Important LA School Board Election on May 21</h3>\n\n<p>On May 25, families in the east San Fernando Valley have the opportunity to vote for who will represent our community on the Los Angeles Unified School District (LAUSD) board. This is a very important election, not only for our school but for the future of our public schools and parent choice in Los Angeles.\nThe board makes major decisions that affect our school and our kids. This includes whether our charter school will be renewed and whether new charter schools can open and they have oversight of how our charter school is run - special education, budget and more.\nWe encourage everyone to get informed about this important election and to vote on May 21!\n<strong>May 6 is the deadline to register to vote.</strong> If you aren\'t already registered, we have forms in our school office. You can also easily register to vote online at www.sos.ca.gov or by picking up a form at your county elections office, library, or U.S. Post Office.\nLearn more at <a href="/la2013">www.ccsafamilies.org/la2013</a>.</p>\n\n<h3>Elección Importante para la Junta Escolar en el 21 de mayo</h3>\n\n<p>En el 21 de mayo, los votantes del este del Valle de San Fernando tendrán la oportunidad de votar para la persona que va a representarnos en la Junta Directiva del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Los Ángeles (LAUSD). Esta es una elección muy importante no solo para nuestra escuela sino para el futuro de la educación pública en Los Angeles.\nLos miembros de la Junta Directiva toman decisiones que afectan a nuestros niños y nuestras escuelas. Incluyen si se renovará el permiso a nuestras escuelas o se cerrarán y si una nueva escuela chárter puede abrir. También vigilan cómo operan nuestras escuelas chárter, desde los programas de educación especial hasta el presupuesto.\nAlentamos a todos informarse sobre la elección y ¡Votemos el 21 de mayo!\n<strong>El 6 de mayo el la fecha limite para registrarse para votar.</strong> El 6 de mayo la fecha límite para registrarse para votar. Tenemos los formularios en la oficina de la escuela. Usted puede registrarse para votar en línea en www.sos.ca.gov o puede también recoger un formulario en la oficina electoral de su condado, bibliotecas locales, u oficinas de correo.\nAprende más en <a href="/la2013">www.ccsafamilies.org/la2013</a>.</p>\n', 'For your Newsletter: LAUSD Elections on May 21', 'A great way to spread the word about the elections is to include information in your school\'s newsletter. Feel free to adjust this text to reflect your school!\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'for_your_newsletter_lausd_elections_on_may_21', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:18', '2016-01-13 04:22:18', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/for_your_newsletter_lausd_elections_on_may_21/', 0, 'post', '', 0) ;
