(630, 1, '2016-01-08 05:49:57', '2016-01-08 05:49:57', 'We are working in communities across California.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nWhere We Organize (page)\r\nWe are working in communities across California.\r\n\r\nOur primary focus areas are:\r\nLos Angeles\r\nRiverside and San Bernadino\r\nSan Jose\r\nRichmond\r\nSacramento\r\nOakland\r\n\r\nHelp Your Community\r\nWherever you live, we want to work with you.� Get in touch and an Organizer will contact you about how you can help improve education where you live.', 'Where We Organize', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '442-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-08 05:49:57', '2016-01-08 05:49:57', '', 442, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/442-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(631, 1, '2016-01-08 19:40:31', '2016-01-08 19:40:31', '<figure class="figure-full figure-border">[<img alt="Redwood_City_parents_celebrate_new_charters.png" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/Redwood%20parents%20celebrate.png" width="491" height="323" class="mt-image-none" style="" />](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BG775rz1HJ4)</figure>\r\nLast month, after two years of working to bring new charter school options to their community, parents celebrated the approval of two new charter schools by the Redwood City School Board. The school board unanimously voted to allow Rocketship Education and KIPP Bay Area Schools to establish new charter schools, which together expect to enroll 1,500 students. It\'s the latest example of parent power fueling the charter school movement.\r\nThe parents in Redwood City are part of Innovate Public Schools, a school reform organization focused on making sure that low-income students and children of color in the greater Silicon Valley region receive an excellent education that will prepare them for success in life. Learn more at [www.innovateschools.org](http://www.innovateschools.org).\r\n\r\n[Watch this touching video of parents realizing that their hard work has finally paid off](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BG775rz1HJ4).\r\n', 'Parents Celebrate Two New Charters', 'A two-year journey brings great schools to Redwood City.\r\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '297-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-08 19:40:31', '2016-01-08 19:40:31', '', 297, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/297-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(632, 1, '2016-01-08 19:42:18', '2016-01-08 19:42:18', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BG775rz1HJ4"><img alt="Redwood_City_parents_celebrate_new_charters.png" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/Redwood%20parents%20celebrate.png" width="491" height="323" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure> Last month, after two years of working to bring new charter school options to their community, parents celebrated the approval of two new charter schools by the Redwood City School Board. The school board unanimously voted to allow Rocketship Education and KIPP Bay Area Schools to establish new charter schools, which together expect to enroll 1,500 students. It\'s the latest example of parent power fueling the charter school movement. The parents in Redwood City are part of Innovate Public Schools, a school reform organization focused on making sure that low-income students and children of color in the greater Silicon Valley region receive an excellent education that will prepare them for success in life. Learn more at &#91;www.innovateschools.org&#93;(http://www.innovateschools.org). &#91;Watch this touching video of parents realizing that their hard work has finally paid off&#93;(https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BG775rz1HJ4).</p>\n', 'Parents Celebrate Two New Charters', 'A two-year journey brings great schools to Redwood City.\r\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '297-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-08 19:42:18', '2016-01-08 19:42:18', '', 297, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/297-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
