(1036, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="West_Contra_Costa_parents.jpeg (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/10/West_Contra_Costa_parents-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nUn mes después de que empezó el año escolar, María estaba muy frustrada que Lincoln Elementary - una escuela tradicional del distrito en West Contra Costa - todavía no le hubiera encontrado un maestro para la clase bilingüe de su hijo, Javier.  El maestro sustituto, quien no era un instructor bilingüe, no servía.  Para ayuda en encontrar una escuela chárter para su hijo María recurrió a Yannell Selman, organizadora de padres para Familias de CCSA.\nPero Yannell decidió ayudar a María a enfrentar el problema en su escuela actual.  María se reunió con docenas de madres en su casa y, con la ayuda de Yannell, ellas decidieron presentar el tema juntas en la próxima reunión de la junta escolar.  Las madres pasaron unos días preparando su presentación.  El día de la reunión más de 15 familias, incluso varios niños y dos maestros, exigieron que la junta encontrara un maestro que fuera permanente y tuviera credenciales para la clase del tercer grado.  Al final de la reunión el personal del distrito estaba completamente dispuesto a ayudarles a las familias.\nAl día siguiente, 45 familias se juntaron en la escuela para escuchar el plan del distrito.  Asombrosamente, el distrito había encontrado un maestro de tiempo completo en menos de 24 horas después de que las familias habían exigido acción de la junta escolar.  The Richmond Confidential, el periódico local, <a href="http://richmondconfidential.org/2014/09/26/after-five-weeks-of-substitutes-3rd-graders-at-lincoln-elementary-school-finally-have-a-permanent-teacher/">escribió un artículo increíble sobre la victoria de los padres.   </a>\nAhora, estas madres de Lincoln están listas para seguir abogando para mejores escuelas.  Han formado un equipo fuerte; saben que el cambio es posible y están preparadas a realizarlo en West Contra Costa.</p>\n', 'Padres del condado de West Contra Costa exigen mejores resultados - ¡y los reciben!', 'Cuando padres de una escuela tradicional necesitaron apoyo, recurrieron a Familias de CCSA.  Y el resto, como se dice, es historia.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '319-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '', 319, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/319-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1037, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '<p>For the first time, thanks in part to your advocacy, a law sponsored by the California Charter Schools Association was passed by the Assembly and the Senate and signed by the governor. AB 948 will enable more charter schools, particularly those serving low-income students, to secure safe, reliable facilities.\nThe governor also vetoed two bills, SB 1263 and AB 913, that would have crippled the independence of charter schools.\nThank you to the hundreds of charter school families who sent emails, letters and faxes in support of the charter school movement. Our collective advocacy helped make this legislative session a huge success!</p>\n', 'You Made a Difference in State Charter School Law', 'Families across California helped make this the most successful legislative session in recent history for charter schools.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '318-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '', 318, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/318-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1038, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Camino_Nuevo_parents.jpeg (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/10/Camino_Nuevo_parents-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nThey started lining up the night before the school board meeting. Parents at some of L.A.\'s leading charter schools assembled on the sidewalk outside the district\'s downtown headquarters. Knowing the next day\'s board meeting would be packed, they went the extra mile by camping out all night to make sure they would make it into the meeting to show their support for their schools.\nThe next day, October 14, 2014, the school board voted on whether to renew charters run by Alliance, Aspire, Camino Nuevo, Crown Prep and New Village. More than 300 parents, clad in colorful school t-shirts, packed the board room, waiting to make their case to the board.\nThey didn\'t have to say a word. Their presence said it all. The board voted to approve all seven schools. Parents cheered, hugged, high-fived and then went back to their families, at ease knowing that their children would continue to attend the excellent schools they\'d chosen.</p>\n', 'L.A. Parents Help Charter Schools Get Renewed', 'As the L.A. school board voted on the renewal of seven charter schools, parents gathered to show their support. The board voted yes to all seven!\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '317-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '', 317, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/317-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1039, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Abby Cole &amp; Barbara Ames.JPG (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/10/Abby Cole &amp; Barbara Ames-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\n"For the first time in my life, I feel I can make a truly educated vote for school board members!" That\'s what Abby Cole, a charter school parent, said after a forum for the five candidates running for the San Juan Unified School District school board.\nCole and parents from 10 charter schools attended a public forum earlier this month organized by parents at Golden Valley Charter School and CCSA Families organizer Joanne Ahola.  The idea is to ensure that community members are following the November 4th school board election. Cole says she has already learned a lot about the candidates\' opinions on key education issues, including if and how they\'ll support high-performing charter schools.\nAre you following your local school board race? Charter schools have a lot to gain or lose in races across the state. Please vote on November 4th. Find out where the candidates in your area stand on charter school issues by <a href="http://www.ccsaadvocates.org/">visiting our sister organization, CCSA Advocates.</a></p>\n', 'San Juan Parents Organize School Board Candidate Forum', '"For the first time in my life, I feel I can make a truly educated vote for school board members!"-Abby Cole, charter school parent\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '316-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '', 316, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/316-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1040, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="West_Contra_Costa_parents.jpeg (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/10/West_Contra_Costa_parents-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nA month after the school year began, Maria was deeply frustrated that Lincoln Elementary - a traditional district school in West Contra Costa - still hadn\'t found a teacher for her son Javier\'s bilingual class. The substitute teacher, who was not a bilingual instructor, wasn\'t cutting it. Maria turned to Yannell Selman, a parent organizer for CCSA Families, for help finding a charter school for her son.\nBut Yannell decided to help Maria address the issue at her school. Maria gathered a dozen mothers in her home and, working with Yannell, they decided to raise the issue together at the next school board meeting. They spent a few days preparing to make their case. On the day of the meeting, more than 15 families, including several children, plus two teachers, called on the board to find a permanent, credentialed teacher for the third grade class. By the end of the meeting, the district staff were practically tripping over themselves to help the families.\nThe very next day, 45 families gathered at the school ready to hear the district\'s plan. Amazingly, the district had found a full-time teacher less than 24 hours after the families had demanded action from the board. The Richmond Confidential, the local newspaper, <a href="http://richmondconfidential.org/2014/09/26/after-five-weeks-of-substitutes-3rd-graders-at-lincoln-elementary-school-finally-have-a-permanent-teacher/">wrote an amazing story about the parent victory</a>.\nNow, these Lincoln moms are ready to continue advocating for better schools. They have formed a strong team; they know change is possible and they are ready to make it happen in West Contra Costa.</p>\n', 'West Contra Costa Parents Demand Better - and Get It!', 'When parents at a traditional school needed advocacy help, they turned to CCSA Families. The rest, as they say, is history.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '315-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 315, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/315-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1041, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '<p>Las escuelas públicas de Thrive abrieron después de esperar 18 meses para la aprobación de su solicitud de chárter.  La escuela primaria (k-8) va a ofrecer una experiencia pública que integra la tecnología a través del Aprendizaje Basado en los Proyectos, la instrucción de propuestas específicas, la educación en el hogar, y la modificación constante para cumplir con las necesidades individuales de los estudiantes.  <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GCtFNaUWAf4">¡Mire el video y aprenda más! </a>\nLa nueva escuela de La Academia de Albert Einstein inauguró su primer año escolar con un gran éxito.  La misión de Einstein es apoyar, cultivar e inspirar a pensadores críticos y multilingües que son ciudadanos completos, responsables y globales.  Serán estudiantes únicamente preparados en prosperar, dirigir y crear cambio positivo en el siglo 21.  <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Llkcs8kd4xA">Mire el video y aprenda de esta emocionante escuela nueva.  </a></p>\n', 'Conozca a dos de la nuevas escuelas más interesantes de San Diego', 'Thrive y Einstein son dos adiciones poderosas a la comunidad de escuelas chárter de San Diego.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '314-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 314, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/314-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1042, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="http://www.ccsa.org/one-movement-many-voices-video-contest.html?utm_source=ommv&amp;utm_medium=go"><img alt="Enter_Video_Contest.png (Homepage Feature: Large)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/09/OMMV-textonly-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_featured_primary.jpg" width="410" height="304" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure>\nCCSA quiere que usted entregue un video original y creativo para el concurso de "Un movimiento.  Muchas voces." ("OMMV: One movement.  Many voices.")  Envíenos su historia de cómo una escuela chárter le ha impactado a usted y su familia.  Puede ser que gane un premio de efectivo para usted y su escuela también.  <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/blog/2014/09/one-movement-many-voices-video-contest---spread-the-word.html">Consiga toda la información para que se pueda entrar en el concurso.  </a></p>\n', 'Entre en el concurso de video de CCSA', 'Comparta su historia de cómo una escuela chárter de California le ha impactado positivamente.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '313-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 313, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/313-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1043, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="http://www.ccsa.org/advocacy/accountability/portraitofthemovement/?utm_source=portraitofthemovement&amp;utm_medium=go"><img alt="Portrait_of_a_Movement_2014.png (Homepage Feature: Large)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/09/POM-2014-med-top-1-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_featured_primary.jpg" width="410" height="304" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure>\nEl cuarto anual "Retrato del movimiento" de CCSA cuenta la historia del grande y diverso movimiento de las escuelas chárter de California que ahora sirve a medio millón de estudiantes de escuelas públicas.  Cada año crece más mientras hace mejoras significativas en el rendimiento académico.  <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/advocacy/accountability/portraitofthemovement/?utm_source=portraitofthemovement&amp;utm_medium=go">Eche un vistazo.</a></p>\n', '"Retrato del movimiento"  muestra que las escuelas chárter están haciendo progreso', 'Decenas de miles de estudiantes están recibiendo educación en escuelas chárter que son mejores que las de hace solo cinco años.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '312-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 312, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/312-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1044, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="http://www.ccsa.org/advocacy/accountability/portraitofthemovement/?utm_source=portraitofthemovement&amp;utm_medium=go"><img alt="Portrait_of_a_Movement_2014.png (Homepage Feature: Large)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/09/POM-2014-med-top-1-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_featured_primary.jpg" width="410" height="304" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure>\nCCSA\'s fourth annual "Portrait of the Movement" tells the story of the large and diverse California charter schools movement now serving a half million public school students and growing every year while making significant improvements in academic performance. <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/blog/2014/08/ccsa-issues-report-showing-charters-making-significant-academic-gains.html?mkt_tok=3RkMMJWWfF9wsRoluK7OZKXonjHpfsX56esvUa60lMI%2F0ER3fOvrPUfGjI4CTcRqI%2BSLDwEYGJlv6SgFTrfMMaNvzbgIXxI%3D">Take a look.</a></p>\n', '"Portrait of the Movement" Shows Charters Making Gains', 'Tens of thousands of students are being educated in better performing charter schools than just five years ago.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '311-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 311, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/311-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1045, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="http://www.ccsa.org/one-movement-many-voices-video-contest.html?utm_source=ommv&amp;utm_medium=go"><img alt="Enter_Video_Contest.png (Homepage Feature: Large)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/09/OMMV-textonly-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_featured_primary.jpg" width="410" height="304" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure>\nCCSA wants you to submit an original and creative video for the One Movement. Many Voices. (OMMV) Video Contest! Send us your story about how a charter school has impacted you and your family. You could win a cash prize for yourself and your school. <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/one-movement-many-voices-video-contest.html?utm_source=ommv&amp;utm_medium=go&amp;mkt_tok=3RkMMJWWfF9wsRoluK7OZKXonjHpfsX56esvUa60lMI%2F0ER3fOvrPUfGjI4CTcRqI%2BSLDwEYGJlv6SgFTrfMMaNvzbgIXxI%3D">Get all the info so you can enter!</a></p>\n', 'Enter CCSA\'s Video Contest', 'Share your story of how a California charter school has positively impacted you.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '310-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 310, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/310-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1046, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Thrive_San_Diego_Opening_Video.png (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/09/Screen Shot 2014-09-15 at 11.03.05 AM-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nThrive Public Schools opened this year after an 18-month journey for its charter petition\'s approval. The K-8 school will offer an educational experience that integrates technology through Project Based Learning, targeted instruction, homeschooling, and tinkering to meet individual student needs. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GCtFNaUWAf4&amp;list=UUuatukE6VTyzMqKIaJDGXlg&amp;mkt_tok=3RkMMJWWfF9wsRoluK7OZKXonjHpfsX56esvUa60lMI%2F0ER3fOvrPUfGjI4CTcRqI%2BSLDwEYGJlv6SgFTrfMMaNvzbgIXxI%3D">Watch the video and learn more!</a>\nAlbert Einstein Academies\' new middle school kicked off its first school year with a bang. Einstein\'s mission is to nurture, cultivate and inspire multilingual, critical thinkers who are well-rounded, responsible, global citizens uniquely prepared to thrive, lead and create positive change in the 21st century. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Llkcs8kd4xA&amp;list=UUuatukE6VTyzMqKIaJDGXlg&amp;mkt_tok=3RkMMJWWfF9wsRoluK7OZKXonjHpfsX56esvUa60lMI%2F0ER3fOvrPUfGjI4CTcRqI%2BSLDwEYGJlv6SgFTrfMMaNvzbgIXxI%3D">Watch the video and get a taste of this exciting new school. </a></p>\n', 'Meet Two of San Diego\'s Most Exciting New Schools', 'Thrive and Einstein are two powerful new additions to the San Diego charter school community.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '309-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 309, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/309-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1047, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Parents_at_Luskin_in_LA.jpg (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/08/Parents at Luskin in LA-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nLas familias de las escuelas chárter de Los Ángeles aportaron energía y compromiso tremendos a las elecciones especiales de ayer de la Junta Escolar del Distrito 1.  Durante los últimos meses los padres participaron en un foro de los candidatos y muchas actividades de sacar el voto que aumentaron conciencia - no solo con respecto de la carrera sino también de la necesidad de que la Junta Escolar de LAUSD apoye escuelas chárter de alta calidad.\nEn la carrera, Dr. George McKenna - quien ganó con 53% del voto - y Alex Johnson expresaron apoyo para las escuelas públicas, ambos chárter y tradicional,  que mejoran el rendimiento estudiantil.\nEsta elección vio un nuevo nivel de pasión de las familias de las escuelas chárter dentro del Distrito 1 y más allá también.  Las familias de las escuelas chárter van a seguir apoyando la expansión de las escuelas chárter de alta calidad  y la opción educativa para servir a estudiantes en todos los códigos postales.\n¡Gracias por ser parte de la elección y en recordar a todos que las voces de las familias de las escuelas chárter importan!</p>\n', 'Familias chárter energizan la carrera para la Junta Escolar de L.A.', 'En las elecciones de la Junta Escolar del Distrito 1 de LAUSD se vio un nuevo nivel de pasión y dedicación de los padres de las escuelas chárter.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '308-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 308, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/308-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1048, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Yannell_Selman.JPG (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/08/Yannell Selman-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nYannell Selman se juntó con California Charter Schools Association en junio de 2014 como Organizador de Padres para las cinco escuelas chárter en el distrito de Richmond.  Ella está orgullosa de que las escuelas con que trabaja - cada una sirviendo más que nada a los estudiantes de bajos recursos - están consiguiendo mejores resultados que escuelas tradicionales.\nEn esta importante posición de apoyo para las escuelas chárter,  Yannell está construyendo un equipo de padres informados, activos y fortalecidos con respecto de los temas educativos que afectan a los estudiantes.\nSu pasión para la organización comunitaria empezó cuando enseñó una clase del segundo grado en una escuela pública de Richmond.  Trabajó duro para prepararles a sus estudiantes para la escuela,  pero llegó a sentirse frustrada al verlos seguir a clases con profesores a quienes no les importaba el futuro de sus estudiantes.  Yannell se desanimó al aprender que los padres vieron este tipo de comportamiento de profesor como algo normal en la educación pública.\nDespués de ver el éxito de tantos de sus estudiantes que cambiaron de las tradicionales escuelas públicas a las de chárter, Yannell decidió juntarse al movimiento de las escuelas chárter.  Le encanta fortalecer a los padres a tomar acción y asegurar que sus hijos tengan una opción en las escuelas a que asisten y que reciban una educación de calidad de los profesores a los cuales sí les importa.\nAntes de su trabajo como profesora, Yannell participó en el trabajo de organización en países como Bolivia, Honduras y Chile como parte de su cursado universitario en Northwestern University. Cuando no está trabajando le gusta hacer ejercicio.  Ha participado en media maratones y también practica cross-fit y el levantamiento de pesas.  Yannell también es certificada en el buceo y le gusta jugar ajedrez.</p>\n', 'Conozca a nuestro equipo: Yannell Selman', 'Un ex profesor bilingüe, Yannell trabaja con los padres en cinco escuelas chárter en Richmond.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '307-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 307, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/307-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1049, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Advocates_at_Capitol.jpg (Homepage Feature: Large)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/08/Advocates at capitol-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_featured_primary.jpg" width="410" height="304" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nYou did it! Because of signatures, faxes and phone calls from charter school families, teachers and school leaders, <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/advocacy/statewide/ab948.html?utm_source=advocacy/statewide/ab948&amp;utm_medium=go">AB 948</a> was pulled off of suspense today -- moving California one step closer to facilities funding for more charter schools.\nThis important bill would provide many more low-income students with access to high quality learning environments. Let\'s keep the momentum going until it\'s signed!</p>\n', 'Big Win for Charter School Facilities Funding', 'You did it! A crucial charter school facilities bill, AB 948, is moving forward thanks to our collective advocacy.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '305-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 305, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/305-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1050, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Yannell_Selman.JPG (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/08/Yannell Selman-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nYannell Selman joined California Charter Schools Association in June 2014 as a Parent Organizer for the five charter schools in the Richmond district. She is proud that the schools she works with - each one serving primarily low-income students - are currently outperforming traditional schools.\nIn this important role supporting charter school advocacy, Yannell is building a team of parents who are informed, active and empowered around educational issues that affect students.\nHer passion for community organizing began when she taught a bilingual second grade class in a Richmond public school. She worked hard to prepare her students for school, yet became frustrated seeing them go into classes with teachers who did not care about the students\' futures. Yannell wad discouraged to learn that parents thought this kind of teacher behavior was the norm in public education.\nAfter seeing so many of her traditional public school students\' siblings excel in charter schools, Yannell decided to join the charter school movement. She loves empowering parents to take action and assure their children have a choice in the schools they attend and receive a quality education from teachers who care.\nBefore her work as a teacher, Yannell participated in organizing work abroad in countries such as Bolivia, Honduras and Chile as part of her undergraduate coursework at Northwestern University. When she\'s not working, she enjoys exercising and fitness. She has participated in half-marathons and practices cross-fit and weight lifting training. Yannell is also SCUBA certified and enjoys playing chess.</p>\n', 'Meet Our Team: Yannell Selman', 'A former bilingual teacher, Yannell works with parents at five charter schools in Richmond.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '304-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 304, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/304-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1051, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Parents_at_Luskin_in_LA.jpg (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/08/Parents at Luskin in LA-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nLos Angeles charter school families brought tremendous energy and engagement to yesterday\'s special election in Board District 1. During the past few months, parents participated in a candidate forum and numerous get-out-the-vote activities that raised awareness -- not just about the race, but also about the need for the LAUSD board to support high quality charter schools.\nIn the race, Dr. George McKenna -- who won with 53% of the vote -- and Alex Johnson expressed support for public schools, both charter and traditional, that improve student achievement.\nThis election saw a new level of passion from charter school families across Board District 1 and beyond. Charter school families will continue to advocate for the expansion of high quality charter schools and educational choice in order to serve students in every zip code.\nThank you for being part of the election and reminding everyone that charter school families\' voices matter!</p>\n', 'Charter Families Energize L.A. School Board Race', 'The election in LAUSD\'s Board District 1 saw a new level of passion and engagement from charter school parents.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '303-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 303, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/303-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1052, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="http://sanfrancisco.cbslocal.com/video/10313059-students-rising-above-carlene-ervin/#.U7GYqFA-F7I.twitter"><img alt="Aspire_grad_foster_youth_valedictorian.png" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/Aspire_grad_foster_youth_valedictorian.png" width="528" height="330" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure>\nDisfrute estas tres historias de los graduados de las escuelas chárter de California del 2014.  ¡Ganaron una impresionante cobertura de los medios con sus logros inspiradores!\nCBS llegó a conocer a Carlene Ervin, una estudiante en acogida de la San Francisco Aspire College Prep.  <a href="http://sanfrancisco.cbslocal.com/video/10313059-students-rising-above-carlene-ervin/#.U7GYqFA-F7I.twitter">Se graduó primera en su clase y ahora se va a estudiar a Yale</a>.  NBC relató la historia de Kelly Chambers, una estudiante de Classical Academy High School en San Diego, quien ahora <a href="http://www.nbcsandiego.com/video/#!/on-air/as-seen-on/Inspirational-Student-Kelly-Chambers/261164511">pasa sus veranos viajando a países en vías de desarrollo para proveer cuidado médico y educación</a>.  Y la L.A. Daily News hizo una historia fenomenal de Ashley Cunningham, una graduada de Granada Hills Charter High School que ya se ha convertido en <a href="http://www.dailynews.com/social-affairs/20140706/granada-hills-charter-grad-cooks-her-way-to-college">una cocinera exitosa que está escalando posiciones y competiendo por el nivel nacional</a>.\nBravo a estos estudiantes sobresalientes y los profesores, los directores y las comunidades de escuelas chárter que les han apoyado a lo largo de sus trayectos.</p>\n', 'Los graduados de las escuelas chárter llegan a ser noticia', 'Un cocinero, un estudiante en acogida graduado con las mejores calificaciones y un voluntario médico global.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '302-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 302, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/302-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1053, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Katie_Taylor_Oakland_2.JPG (Homepage Feature: Large)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/07/Katie_Taylor_Oakland_2-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_featured_primary.jpg" width="410" height="304" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nKatie Taylor se juntó a nosotros en mayo del 2014 como Organizadora de Padres de 30 escuelas chárter de Oakland, un distrito donde 25% de los estudiantes de escuelas públicas asisten a escuelas chárter.  En esta puesta tan importante Katie trabaja con padres para que sean defensores de la educación de sus hijos y para que influyan el paisaje político.\nKatie es apasionada por trabajar en un distrito escolar que siempre ha tenido rendimiento inferior y por ayudar en dar poder a los estudiantes para que puedan asistir a la universidad y entrar al mundo de negocios.  Cree fuertemente que una sociedad productiva necesita un fuerte sistema educativo.  Si los padres son fortalecidos con información, dice ella, las escuelas mejoran, los barrios llegan a ser más seguros y los negocios tienen éxito.  Katie está emocionada sobre el aspecto del desarrollo comunitario de su trabajo y por trabajar directamente con los padres para ayudarles a navegar el sistema educativo.\nAntes de juntarse con CCSA, Katie trabajó para la Women\'s Initiatives for Self-Employment (iniciativas de mujeres para el trabajo autónomo), una organización sin fines de lucro que ayudó a que crecieran las mujeres y que desarrollaran sus propios negocios.  Está orgullosa que por cuatro años hizo sentir poderosas a las mujeres con respecto de ser agentes de cambio en sus propias vidas.\nKatie vive en Oakland donde pasa mucho de su tiempo libre.  Asiste a las fiestas comunitarias de "First Friday" (primer viernes del mes) cada mes donde tiene interacciones con negocios locales y miembros de la comunidad.  También disfruta en pasar tiempo fon su familia y su perro.  Tiene planes de volver a su amor por el baile contemporáneo/moderno.</p>\n', 'Conoce nuestro equipo: Katie Taylor', 'Si usted es padre en Oakland, Katie puede ser su mejor aliado.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '301-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 301, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/301-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1054, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="McKenna_and_Alex_Johnson_BD1.png" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/McKenna_and_Alex_Johnson_BD1.png" width="385" height="294" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nLos padres de las escuelas chárter están centrados en una elección importante del próximo mes que puede llegar a transformar el comité escolar de Los Ángeles Unified.  Dos candidatos - consejero educativo <a href="http://alexjohnsonforlaschoolboard.com/">Alex Johnson</a> y el ex director <a href="http://www.electmckenna.com/">George McKenna</a> - están tratando de ganar la puesta en el Distrito del comité 1, una zona que siempre ha sido desatendida y que nunca ha producido buenos resultados.\nSin embargo las escuelas chárter de la zona han producido mejoras impresionantes para estudiantes latinos y afroamericanos, entonces los padres quieren asegurar que el candidato que gane es un defensor fuerte de las escuelas chárter.\nSi usted es votante del BD1 (Distrito del comité 1), <a href="http://registertovote.ca.gov//">asegúrese que esté registrado a votar</a>.  Tiene hasta el 28 de julio para registrar.\n<a href="http://www.ccsaadvocates.org/">Visite Defensores de CCSA (CCSA Advocates) para saber qué candidato apoya nuestra organización hermanada</a>.</p>\n', 'Los padres enfocan en la competencia de la Junta Escolar de L.A.', '¿Va a apoyar las escuelas chárter el ganador?\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '300-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '', 300, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/300-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1055, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '<p>Si usted cree que un excelente programa de artes no puede producir resultados académicos sobresalientes, hay que pensarlo otra vez.  Además de proveer un programa de artes excepcional a estudiantes quienes son mayoritariamente de familias de bajos recursos y sin experiencia anterior en las artes, Renaissance Arts Academy en Los Ángeles también tiene una taza de graduado de 100%.  Este año el Comité de Universidad prestó atención y eligió a RenArts <a href="https://artsaward.collegeboard.org/past-winners.php?ep_mid=10936551&amp;ep_rid=38975792">para su Premio de Excelencia e Innovación en las Artes del 2014</a>.  ¡Bien hecho!</p>\n', 'Y el ganador es...', 'Una escuela chárter de L.A. recibe un honor nacional por su programa de artes\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '299-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '', 299, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/299-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1056, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BG775rz1HJ4"><img alt="Redwood_City_parents_celebrate_new_charters.png" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/Redwood%20parents%20celebrate.png" width="491" height="323" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure>\nEl mes pasado, después de dos años de trabajo en traer nuevas opciones de escuelas chárter a su comunidad, los padres celebraron la aprobación de dos nuevas escuelas chárter por el comité de escuelas de Redwood City.  El comité votó por unanimidad dejar "Rocketship Education" y "KIPP Bay Area Schools" a establecer dos nuevas escuelas chárter, que juntas esperan inscribir a 1.500 estudiantes.  Es el ejemplo más reciente del poder de los padres en alimentar el movimiento de las escuelas chárter.\n<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BG775rz1HJ4">Mire este video conmovedor de los padres dándose cuenta de que su trabajo arduo se ha visto recompensado</a>.</p>\n', 'Los padres celebran dos nuevas escuelas chárter', 'Un viaje de dos años trae escuelas geniales a Redwood.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '298-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '', 298, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/298-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1057, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="http://sanfrancisco.cbslocal.com/video/10313059-students-rising-above-carlene-ervin/#.U7GYqFA-F7I.twitter"><img alt="Aspire_grad_foster_youth_valedictorian.png" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/Aspire_grad_foster_youth_valedictorian.png" width="528" height="330" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure>\nEnjoy these three stories of \'14 California charter school graduates whose inspirational achievements earned them some impressive media coverage!\nCBS got to know Carlene Ervin, a foster student at San Francisco\'s Aspire College Prep who graduated first in her class and <a href="http://sanfrancisco.cbslocal.com/video/10313059-students-rising-above-carlene-ervin/#.U7GYqFA-F7I.twitter">is now headed to Yale</a>. NBC profiled Kelly Chambers, a student at Classical Academy High School in San Diego who <a href="http://www.nbcsandiego.com/video/#!/on-air/as-seen-on/Inspirational-Student-Kelly-Chambers/261164511">spends her summers traveling to undeveloped countries</a> to provide medical care and education.\nAnd the L.A. Daily News has a great piece on Granada Hills Charter High School grad Ashley Cunningham, a chef who\'s already <a href="http://www.dailynews.com/social-affairs/20140706/granada-hills-charter-grad-cooks-her-way-to-college">climbing the professional ladder and competing nationally</a>.\nBravo to these outstanding students and the teachers, principals and charter school communities that supported them along the way!</p>\n', 'Charter Grads Make Headlines', 'A chef, a valedictorian foster student and a global medical volunteer.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '296-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '', 296, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/296-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1058, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Ren_Arts_students.png (Homepage Feature: Large)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/07/Ren_Arts_students-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_featured_primary.jpg" width="410" height="304" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nIf you think a great arts program can\'t deliver outstanding academic results, think again. Besides providing an exceptional arts program to students who are mostly low-income and have no prior experience in the arts, <a href="http://www.renarts.org/">Renaissance Arts Academy in Los Angeles</a> also boasts a 100% graduation rate. This year, the College Board took notice, selecting RenArts for their <a href="https://artsaward.collegeboard.org/past-winners.php?ep_mid=10936551&amp;ep_rid=38975792">2014 Award for Excellence and Innovation in the Arts</a>. Way to go!</p>\n', 'And the Winner Is...', 'L.A. charter school receives national honor for its arts program.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '295-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '', 295, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/295-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1059, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="McKenna_and_Alex_Johnson_BD1.png" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/McKenna_and_Alex_Johnson_BD1.png" width="385" height="294" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nCharter school parents are focused on an important election next month that could reshape the Los Angeles Unified school board. Two candidates - education advisor <a href="http://alexjohnsonforlaschoolboard.com/">Alex Johnson</a> and former principal <a href="http://www.electmckenna.com/">George McKenna</a> - are vying for the seat in Board District 1, an area that has been chronically under-served and under-performing.\nCharter schools in the area, however, have yielded impressive gains for Latino and African American students, so parents want to make sure the candidate who wins is a strong supporter of charter schools.\nIf you\'re a voter in BD1, make sure you\'re <a href="http://registertovote.ca.gov//">registered to vote</a>. You have until July 28 to register.\n<a href="http://www.ccsaadvocates.org/">Visit CCSA Advocates to find out which candidate our sister organization has endorsed</a>.</p>\n', 'Parents Target L.A. School Board Race', 'Will the winner be a supporter of charter schools?\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '294-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '', 294, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/294-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1061, 10, '2016-01-13 04:53:37', '2016-01-13 04:53:37', '<p>The scene is becoming more common. Each month at the meeting of the school board of the Los Angeles Unified School, District make hundreds of families outside row only for the chance to tell the board how much care about their schools. That is precisely what happened to the meeting this month, parents and students in charter schools Aspire, Camino Nuevo and Green Dot met to ensure that the board voted to renew its charter schools. And that is exactly what made the meeting. L.A. Live charter families! Families are also spreading the word about a substantial problem facing schools of LA: the search for the next superintendent. By filling out hundreds of surveys and attending public meetings, parents and students in charter schools are ensuring that the school board know that the next superintendent must support charter schools and school choice. It is expected that the school board chooses the next superintendent for later this year</p>\n', 'L.A. Families Flex Their Advocacy Muscle', 'The scene is becoming more common. Each month at the meeting of the school board of the Los Angeles Unified School, District make hundreds of families outside row only for the chance to tell the board how much care about their schools.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '394-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:53:37', '2016-01-13 04:53:37', '', 394, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/394-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1062, 10, '2016-01-13 04:53:48', '2016-01-13 04:53:48', '<p>The scene is becoming more common. Each month at the meeting of the school board of the Los Angeles Unified School, District make hundreds of families outside row only for the chance to tell the board how much care about their schools. That is precisely what happened to the meeting this month, parents and students in charter schools Aspire, Camino Nuevo and Green Dot met to ensure that the board voted to renew its charter schools. And that is exactly what made the meeting. L.A. Live charter families! Families are also spreading the word about a substantial problem facing schools of LA: the search for the next superintendent. By filling out hundreds of surveys and attending public meetings, parents and students in charter schools are ensuring that the school board know that the next superintendent must support charter schools and school choice. It is expected that the school board chooses the next superintendent for later this year</p>\n', 'L.A. Families Flex Their Advocacy Muscle', 'The scene is becoming more common. Each month at the meeting of the school board of the Los Angeles Unified School, District make hundreds of families outside row only for the chance to tell the board how much care about their schools.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '394-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:53:48', '2016-01-13 04:53:48', '', 394, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/394-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
