(1133, 3, '2016-01-13 22:39:30', '2016-01-13 22:39:30', '<p>It\'s been said that "education is the civil rights issue of our time," and many parents agree wholeheartedly. That\'s why so many of them have sought out charter schools in order to ensure their children receive the quality education that they need and deserve. A groundbreaking lawsuit last year found that, indeed, the civil rights of low-income students and students of color were being violated by the traditional public education system in California. A forum earlier this month in Sacramento offered a chance to learn more about the Vergara case, named after one of the student plaintiffs, along with other policy issues that impact how much students learn in the classroom. Nine charter school parents, plus a charter teacher, a faith leader and several community members who support charter schools, attended the forum. Representatives from a number of local schools, as well as advocacy organizations like Education Trust-West, attended as well. It was a powerful event that brought people together for sharing and learning, with the goal of removing the obstacles that prevent historically under-served students from getting the great education they deserve.</p>\n', 'Families Engage in Education Civil Rights Discussion', 'Charter families and supporters discussed a historic lawsuit and its implications for student learning in California.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '375-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 22:39:30', '2016-01-13 22:39:30', '', 375, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/375-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1134, 3, '2016-01-13 22:41:22', '2016-01-13 22:41:22', '<p>It\'s been said that "education is the civil rights issue of our time," and many parents agree wholeheartedly. That\'s why so many of them have sought out charter schools in order to ensure their children receive the quality education that they need and deserve. A groundbreaking lawsuit last year found that, indeed, the civil rights of low-income students and students of color were being violated by the traditional public education system in California. A forum earlier this month in Sacramento offered a chance to learn more about the Vergara case, named after one of the student plaintiffs, along with other policy issues that impact how much students learn in the classroom. Nine charter school parents, plus a charter teacher, a faith leader and several community members who support charter schools, attended the forum. Representatives from a number of local schools, as well as advocacy organizations like Education Trust-West, attended as well. It was a powerful event that brought people together for sharing and learning, with the goal of removing the obstacles that prevent historically under-served students from getting the great education they deserve.</p>\n', 'Families Engage in Education Civil Rights Discussion', 'Charter families and supporters discussed a historic lawsuit and its implications for student learning in California.\r\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '375-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 22:41:22', '2016-01-13 22:41:22', '', 375, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/375-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1135, 10, '2016-01-13 22:51:45', '2016-01-13 22:51:45', '<p>We are working in communities across California.<!--more--> Our primary focus areas are:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Los Angeles </li>\n<li>Riverside and San Bernadino </li>\n<li>San Jose </li>\n<li>Richmond </li>\n<li>Sacramento </li>\n<li>Oakland</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Volunteer</h3>\n\n<p>Wherever you live, we want to work with you. Get in touch and an Organizer will contact you about how you can help improve education.</p>\n', 'Where We Organize', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '442-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 22:51:45', '2016-01-13 22:51:45', '', 442, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/442-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1136, 3, '2015-07-29 22:52:45', '2015-07-29 22:52:45', '<p>No hay nada que sea más imporante a los padres que mantener a sus hijos a salvo de daños. Entonces cuando algunos padres decidieron reunirse para hacer una diferencia en su escuela chárter local, su primera prioridad fue mejorar las medidas de la seguridad de tráfico alrededor del campus.</p>\n\n<p>El campus Sandra Cisneros de Nuevo Charter Academy está ubicado justo al lado de una interseción muy congestionada por el famoso Sunset Boulevard de Los Ángeles. Los padres queiren asegurar que los estudiantes que andan a pie a y desde el campus están seguros. Entonces, están reuniéndose para urgir que los oficiales de la ciudad instalen topes de velocidad y señales de tránsito en puntos claves alrededor del campus. También quieren que se haga una calle de un solo sentido para disminuir el tráfico.</p>\n\n<p>En este momento los padres están redactando una solicitud al concejal de L.A. Mitch O\'Farrell, y también están creando una página en Facebook para conseguir apoyo. Felicitaciones a estos padres chárter por comprometerse en su comunidad y con sus oficiales elegidos en uno de los aspectos más importantes de la educación: ¡la seguridad estudiantil!</p>\n\n<p><a href="http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/content/uploads/2016/01/camino_nuevo_parents-cropped.jpg">Camino Nuevo Parents</a></p>\n', 'La seguridad ante todo en escuela chárter de L.A.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'la-seguridad-ante-todo-en-escuela-charter-de-l-a', '', '', '2016-01-20 00:33:31', '2016-01-20 00:33:31', '', 0, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/?p=1136&#038;lang=es', 0, 'post', '', 0),
